gw.api.effdate

Class EffDatedUniqueKey<T extends EffDated>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.domain.AbstractKey
      • gw.api.effdate.EffDatedUniqueKey<T>

  • public class EffDatedUniqueKey<T extends EffDated>
extends AbstractKey
    This class defines a key to uniquely identify EffDated beans based on the set of properties passed in during construction. Given a consistent set of properties per type of EffDatedBean, an EffDatedUniqueKey can represent a key to identify unique and duplicate beans of that type.

    • Constructor Detail

      • EffDatedUniqueKey

        public EffDatedUniqueKey(T effDatedBean,
                         java.lang.Iterable<? extends IEntityPropertyInfo> identityProps)
        Creates an EffDatedUniqueKey for the given EffDated bean based on the bean's intrinsic type and the values of the given identity properties. Two EffDatedUniqueKey will evaluate as equal when:
        • The underlying EffDated bean is the same
        • OR the entity intrinsic types of the beans both match AND the values of all identity properties are also equal
        Parameters:
        effDatedBean - the EffDated to create a unique key for
        identityProps - the properties with which to evaluate the key for equality with another EffDatedUniqueKey

    • Method Detail

      • getEffDated

        public T getEffDated()

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object arg)
        Determines if an EffDatedUniqueKey equals another EffDatedUniqueKey. Two EffDatedUniqueKey will evaluate as equal when:
        • The identity property lists for both keys are the same (see AbstractKey.identityPropertiesEqual)
        • AND the entity intrinsic types of the beans both match AND the values of all identity properties are also equal
        • Having object identity of both EffDated beans will short-circuit to true.
        Overrides:
        equals in class AbstractKey

      • hashCode

        public int hashCode()
        Two objects that compare as equal() must always return the same hashCode(). If the two EffDated properties refer to the same object reference they WILL have the same identity properties, verifying the equals() short-circuit in the special case of EffDated bean identitiy. It is thus allowed to fall back to the super hash code, which essentially calculates the combined hash code of all values (calling overridden method getValueOfIdentityProperty to reflectively retrieve the value of the contained EffDated bean) of the identity properties.
        Overrides:
        hashCode in class AbstractKey
        Returns:
        Hash code calculated over all identity property values
